<p>February 23, 2015</p>
<blockquote><p>But animal rights advocates who are critical of PETA&#8217;s high euthanasia rate say the bill would simply require the Norfolk-based animal rights group to make a better effort at adoption. The bill&#8217;s sponsor, Sen. Bill Stanley, R-Franklin County, called PETA&#8217;s Norfolk operation &#8220;a way station for death&#8221; and said he wants the group to reduce its high euthanasia rate.</p></blockquote>
