<h3>Stanley bills advance to House</h3>
<p>February 6, 2015</p>
<blockquote><p>Several pieces of legislation by state Sen. Bill Stanley, R-Franklin County, are headed to the House of Delegates after passing the Senate.</p></blockquote>
<div class="encrypted-content">
<blockquote><p>One would expand scholarship coverage to medical school students who agree to enter practice in rural, underserved or underprivileged parts of the state. Another would coordinate an advisory council at the state level for patient-centered medical homes. The homes are ways for local patients to effectively receive care through their primary physicians.</p></blockquote>
</div>
<p><a href="http://www.godanriver.com/news/danville/stanley-bills-advance-to-house/article_c163312c-ae57-11e4-b4ad-67f503836745.html">Read More</a></p>
