<h3>Stanley to introduce healthcare reform legislation</h3>
<p>Five proposals aimed at offering citizens options to Obamacare</p>
<p>Monday, December 22, 2014</p>
<blockquote><p>Sen. Bill Stanley (R-Glade Hill) will introduce a series of legislative initiatives for healthcare reform for the 2015 General Assembly session.</p>
<p>These legislative proposals include the creation of a Patient-Centered Medical Home Advisory Council, Private Health Insurance Exchanges, Regional Care Organizations for existing Medicaid patients, Medical Scholarships for doctors who practice in rural areas, and a Rural Healthcare Telemedicine Pilot Program.</p></blockquote>
